5000|$|A {{countervailing duty}} is imposed {{for the purpose}} of {{offsetting}} a subsidy. Subsidies are not prohibited under WTO unless there is evidence of injury or damage to the importing country. The Agreement on Subsidies and <b>Countervailing</b> <b>Measures</b> forms the current regime for imposing countervailing duties on subsidised goods to conform to GATT principles. The Committee on Subsidies and <b>Countervailing</b> <b>Measures</b> exists to carry out tasks assigned under the Agreement ...|$|E
